      action: "Metabolized by colonic bacteria to lactic acid and acetic acid, acidifying the colonic lumen which converts ammonia (NH₃) to ammonium (NH₄⁺), trapping it in the gut lumen for fecal excretion; also acts as osmotic laxative to reduce transit time",
