    pearls: ["Lactulose is the first-line treatment: titrate to 2-3 soft stools per day — over-treatment with diarrhea and dehydration can paradoxically WORSEN HE", "Asterixis (liver flap) is the hallmark physical finding but is NOT present in Grade I or Grade IV HE — too subtle in early disease and absent in coma", "Protein restriction is OUTDATED and harmful — current guidelines recommend normal to high protein intake (1.2-1.5 g/kg/day) as malnutrition worsens outcomes", "Serum ammonia levels do not reliably correlate with the severity of encephalopathy — treat the patient's clinical status, not the ammonia number", "Always look for a precipitating factor: GI bleed, infection, constipation, dehydration, hypokalemia, medications — HE rarely occurs spontaneously", "Rifaximin added to lactulose reduces HE recurrence by >50% and is the standard of care for secondary prophylaxis"],
